## 1. Overview

### 1.1 Purpose
The Professional License Verification System automates the process of managing professional license information by:
- Reading license data from Excel files maintained by researchers
- Storing data in a centralized MongoDB collection (`license_source`)
- Providing REST APIs for CRUD operations
- Enabling smart search capabilities through Elasticsearch integration
- Offering a React-based UI for efficient data management

### 1.2 Current State
Researchers manually maintain and update license information using Excel sheets. This approach is:
- Time-consuming and error-prone
- Inefficient for large volumes of data
- Difficult to search and filter
- Lacks centralized management

### 1.3 Proposed Solution
Implement an automated system following the **same architectural patterns as the Employee Source database**, including:
- Automated Excel file processing
- MongoDB storage with optimized indexes
- Elasticsearch integration for smart search
- RESTful APIs for all operations
- React UI for user interaction

### 1.4 Key Benefits
- ✅ Eliminates repetitive manual data entry
- ✅ Reduces human errors
- ✅ Enables efficient data retrieval with advanced filtering
- ✅ Provides centralized license information management
- ✅ Supports scalable architecture for future enhancements

