  "scope": "STATE",
  "country": "United States",
  "state": "California",
  "license_type": "Medical License",
  "web_address": [
    "https://www.mbc.ca.gov/",
    "https://www.mbc.ca.gov/Licensees/"
  ],
  "phone": [
    "+1-800-633-2322",
    "+1-916-263-2382"
  ],
  "email": [
    "webmaster@mbc.ca.gov"
  ],
  "fax": [
    "+1-916-263-2944"
  ],
  "governing_agency": "Medical Board of California",
  "multi_state": "No",
  "expiration": "Biennial renewal required",
  "license_status": "Active",
  "disciplinary_actions": "Public records available online",
  "additional_information": "Online verification available 24/7",
  "created_date": ISODate("2024-03-24T10:00:00Z"),
  "updated_date": ISODate("2024-03-24T10:00:00Z"),
  "created_by": "researcher_001",
  "updated_by": "researcher_001",
  "active": true
}
```

#### 3.1.3 Field Definitions

| Field Name | Type | Required | Description | Validation Rules |
|------------|------|----------|-------------|------------------|
| `_id` | ObjectId | Auto | MongoDB unique identifier | Auto-generated |
| `hon` | String | Yes | Unique Number (Unique identifier) | Unique, non-empty |
| `scope` | String | Yes | License scope | Enum: GLOBAL, NATIONAL, STATE |
| `country` | String | Yes | Country name | Non-empty |
| `state` | String | Conditional | State/Province name | Required if scope=STATE |
| `license_type` | String | Yes | Type of professional license | Non-empty |
| `web_address` | Array[String] | No | Official website URLs | Valid URLs |
| `phone` | Array[String] | No | Contact phone numbers | Phone format |
| `email` | Array[String] | No | Contact email addresses | Email format |
| `fax` | Array[String] | No | Fax numbers | Phone format |
| `governing_agency` | String | No | Governing/regulatory agency | - |
| `multi_state` | String | No | Multi-state license indicator | - |
| `expiration` | String | No | Expiration/renewal information | - |
| `license_status` | String | No | Current status of license | - |
| `disciplinary_actions` | String | No | Disciplinary action information | - |
| `additional_information` | String | No | Additional notes/information | - |
| `created_date` | ISODate | Auto | Record creation timestamp | Auto-generated |
| `updated_date` | ISODate | Auto | Last update timestamp | Auto-updated |
| `created_by` | String | Auto | User who created record | - |
| `updated_by` | String | Auto | User who last updated record | - |
| `active` | Boolean | Yes | Active/inactive flag | Default: true |

#### 3.1.4 Validation Rules

**Conditional Validation**:
- If `scope` = "STATE", then `state` field is **required**
- If `scope` = "NATIONAL" or "GLOBAL", then `state` field is **optional**

**Enum Values**:
- `scope`: Must be one of ["GLOBAL", "NATIONAL", "STATE"]

#### 3.1.5 MongoDB Indexes

To ensure optimal query performance, the following indexes are created:

| Index Name | Fields | Type | Purpose |
|------------|--------|------|---------|
| `idx_hon_unique` | `hon: 1` | Unique | Primary key, ensure uniqueness |
| `idx_scope` | `scope: 1` | Standard | Filter by scope (GLOBAL/NATIONAL/STATE) |
| `idx_country` | `country: 1` | Standard | Filter by country |
| `idx_state` | `state: 1` | Standard | Filter by state |
| `idx_license_type` | `license_type: 1` | Standard | Filter by license type |
| `idx_governing_agency` | `governing_agency: 1` | Standard | Filter by governing agency |
| `idx_scope_state` | `scope: 1, state: 1` | Compound | Combined scope and state queries |
| `idx_active` | `active: 1` | Standard | Filter active/inactive records |

**Index Creation Commands**:
```javascript
db.license_source.createIndex({ hon: 1 }, { unique: true, name: "idx_hon_unique" });
db.license_source.createIndex({ scope: 1 }, { name: "idx_scope" });
db.license_source.createIndex({ country: 1 }, { name: "idx_country" });
db.license_source.createIndex({ state: 1 }, { name: "idx_state" });
db.license_source.createIndex({ license_type: 1 }, { name: "idx_license_type" });
db.license_source.createIndex({ governing_agency: 1 }, { name: "idx_governing_agency" });
db.license_source.createIndex({ scope: 1, state: 1 }, { name: "idx_scope_state" });
db.license_source.createIndex({ active: 1 }, { name: "idx_active" });
```

